Prompt Claude within the wrapper script
    ./prompt-claude.sh "{{PROMPT}}"

How to initiate deep research
    python deep_research.py "{{PROMPT}}"

Run the local/dev environment
    gcquraishi@MacBook-Pro-3 web-app % npm run dev
    ctrl + c ends it

Redeploy
    vercel --prod


Next steps for Google OAuth:
                                                                                        
  To complete the setup, you need to create Google OAuth credentials:                      
                                                                                           
  1. Go to https://console.cloud.google.com/                                               
  2. Create a new project or select an existing one                                        
  3. Enable the Google+ API (or Identity Toolkit API)                                      
  4. Go to Credentials → Create Credentials → OAuth 2.0 Client ID                          
  5. Configure the OAuth consent screen if prompted                                        
  6. For Application type, select Web application                                          
  7. Add these Authorized redirect URIs:                                                   
    - http://localhost:3000/api/auth/callback/google (for local dev)                       
    - https://yourdomain.com/api/auth/callback/google (for production)                     
  8. Copy the Client ID and Client Secret                                                  
  9. Update web-app/.env.local:                                                            
    - Replace YOUR_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID_HERE with your Client ID                               
    - Replace YOUR_GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET_HERE with your Client Secret 
